# Project specific
# database/ and data/corpus_next.v1.nest are tracked via Git LFS.
# Per-phase preset .nest files (data/measure/corpus_*.nest) are
# regeneration artifacts: re-derivable in minutes by measure_presets.py
# from the LFS-tracked baseline. Do NOT commit them — they'd inflate the
# LFS bandwidth quota every phase. We commit only the JSON checksums and
# metrics next to them.
data/measure/corpus_*.nest
data/measure/*.nest-*

# kdb/ holds the project's knowledge base — ADRs, design notes.
# Tracked. Earlier sessions had it gitignored, which silently dropped
# every architectural decision committed there. Fixed 2026-04-28.

# CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md and CONTRIBUTING.md were template placeholders
# at session start and excluded from tracking. The 2026-04-28 audit
# pass replaced them with real content; they are tracked now.
